1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,079
Is Claire really awake?

2
00:00:12,080 --> 00:00:15,159
<i>Then why haven't you brought her back?</i>

3
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:17,879
<i>What happened to me?
Why do I have Claire's face?</i>

4
00:00:17,880 --> 00:00:18,960
You're not Claire.

5
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:21,679
You're Jinla.

6
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:24,199
<i>You were afraid her grandfather would die,</i>

7
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:26,919
<i>so you decided to let me die instead?</i>

8
00:00:26,920 --> 00:00:28,519
<i>Actually, if Ms. Cha hadn't shown up,</i>

9
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:30,999
<i>I'm sure we could've made Jinla</i>

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,959
<i>go along with our plan.</i>

11
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:35,759
And if Ms. Cha told the chairman,
wouldn't he...

12
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:37,920
We can't ever let him find out.

13
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:40,680
<i>How is Claire?</i>

14
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:42,800
She's awake, sir.

15
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,320
I woke up and didn't see you.

16
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:15,760
Oh no. Did I wake you up?

17
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,000
I'm sorry.

18
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,759
It's fine. I couldn't sleep anyway.

19
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,560
I'm excited about Claire.

20
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:27,640
What are you doing in her room?

21
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:36,320
I thought since Claire has woken up,

22
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,879
and she's coming back soon,

23
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:42,599
I'd come in to check
if her room was in order.

24
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:46,320
If it wasn't, I'd have
the maids redo it tomorrow.

25
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,520
Thank you very much.

26
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:52,560
I didn't think you cared about her too.

27
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,880
So how is it? Is everything in order?

28
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,320
‎Yes.

29
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,880
Then shall we go back to bed?

30
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,520
Or is there still something
you're looking for?

31
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,279
Look for what?

32
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:18,000
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

33
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:21,600
Before the helicopter crash,

34
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,520
Claire said she wanted
to talk to me about you.

35
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:30,840
So I thought maybe you wanted
to look for something.

36
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,320
No.

37
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:38,000
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

38
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,319
It's alright.

39
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:43,720
Chan's bringing Claire back tomorrow.
We can talk about it then.

40
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,960
Is there anything else you need here?

41
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,960
No.

42
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,640
‎Let's go.

43
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,000
‎The weather's good today.

44
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:30,159
- Business looks good.
- Whoa.

45
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,400
Take your pick.

46
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,920
- You got it.
- Here you go.

47
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,560
You got it.

48
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:54,640
YUWADIPHANIT
HAPPY NEW YEAR

49
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,520
Take a look.

50
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,319
Excuse me.

51
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:04,840
What's the date today?

52
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:22,040
Excuse me. What's the date today?

53
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:32,480
Hey. Don't stand in front of my shop.

54
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,880
YEAR OF THE DRAGON

55
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,720
It's already March 20, 2024?

56
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:49,720
Yes.

57
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,920
The 20th?

58
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,319
SEPTEMBER 2023
TAKE MY AUNT TO THE DOCTOR

59
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,800
MARCH 2024

60
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:03,720
‎Six months.

61
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:07,880
Aunt.

62
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,960
Aunt Lin.

63
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:33,960
Aunt?

64
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:49,800
Aunt?

65
00:07:51,960 --> 00:07:53,040
Aunt Lin?

66
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,680
Could she be...

67
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:25,120
Is Sri here?

68
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:28,679
Mom, someone's here for you.

69
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:31,680
- What is it? What?
- Ma'am.

70
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:34,520
It's me, Jin.

71
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:38,280
What?

72
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,359
I'm Jin's friend.

73
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:46,599
Jin told me many times

74
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,639
you took care of her aunt
while she was working.

75
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:52,640
Oh! You're Jin's friend?

76
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,920
So...

77
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:57,239
Are you here to collect money from Jin?

78
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,519
No. I...

79
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:02,079
I went to Jin's house,

80
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:04,279
but no one was there. Where did they go?

81
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:06,119
Wait. What kind of friend are you?

82
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:08,720
Didn't you know she died in a crash?

83
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,320
I know that.

84
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,120
What about Lin, her aunt?

85
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,600
Isn't she alone now?

86
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,840
I came because I was worried about her.

87
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,880
It's sad to talk about.

88
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,120
What is it?

89
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:34,560
Lin...

90
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,960
is dead too.

91
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:46,560
After Jin died, there was
no one to take care of her aunt.

92
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:53,479
Lin? Wake up, Lin.

93
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:56,239
<i>‎She hasn't been taking
‎her Alzheimer's medication.</i>

94
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:58,039
<i>Without her medicine,</i>

95
00:09:58,040 --> 00:10:00,599
<i>- her condition got worse every day.</i>
- Who are you?

96
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,879
I'm Sri, your friend.

97
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,039
Remember me?

98
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,599
<i>But no matter how bad she got...</i>

99
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,599
Come home with me.

100
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,039
<i>- ...Jin's aunt...</i>
- No.

101
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,199
<i>remembered one thing.</i>

102
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,320
I'm waiting for my niece.

103
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,080
My niece went to work.

104
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,520
She'll be back soon.

105
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:31,879
<i>Jin.</i>

106
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:33,639
- Jin, my niece. Jin.
- I'm not her.

107
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:35,120
- Jin.
- I'm not her.

108
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,280
You're not. You're not.

109
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:40,640
Wait! Hold on!

110
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,480
Hold on, Jin!

111
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:50,920
<i>Get her to the hospital!</i>

112
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,119
Hurry!

113
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,640
Get her to the hospital!

114
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:02,640
Aunt.

115
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,920
Did I keep you waiting long?

116
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,720
I'm back now.

117
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,080
I'm right here, Aunt.

118
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,720
I'm sorry.

119
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:32,840
<i>Come and eat.</i>

120
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,640
I made your favorite, mackerel.

121
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,720
Let me hug you. Let me hug you.

122
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,119
<i>You too, come on.</i>

123
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,079
<i>Come on, let me have some.</i>

124
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,519
<i>Wow, it's so good.</i>

125
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:52,320
<i>Your cooking is as amazing as ever, Aunt.</i>

126
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:55,120
I'm sorry.

127
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:14,120
I'm sorry.

128
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:34,800
You.

129
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:40,600
How did you know I was here?

130
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,120
I told you.

131
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:47,120
I have all the information about you.

132
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,080
Don't come near me.

133
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,960
I know you're upset.

134
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,799
But it's not what you think.

135
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:05,800
Will you hear me out?

136
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,400
Of course.

137
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,999
‎I never imagined
‎someone could be so selfish

138
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,839
and do something so evil.

139
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:13,959
‎Hey!

140
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,999
- Hey.
- I said hear me out.

141
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,239
Let go.

142
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:19,000
- Let go.
- Give it to me.

143
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,600
Hey.

144
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,679
Hey, let me go! Ow!

145
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:26,239
- I said hear me out.
- Get off me. Get off me.

146
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,679
- Hey.
- Help! Help me!

147
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,679
This man is hurting me! Help!

148
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:30,919
- Hey.
- Let go.

149
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:34,320
If I say your aunt is still alive,
will you listen to me?

150
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:48,320
‎Stop treating other people's
‎lives and deaths like a joke.

151
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:52,160
How could you say that?

152
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:53,760
Because of you.

153
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:58,319
If you hadn't locked me up in the hospital
to turn me into Ms. Claire,

154
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:00,320
my aunt wouldn't have died.

155
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:04,319
And if I hadn't taken you to the hospital,

156
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,960
you'd be dead by now too.

157
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:09,280
And your aunt really would be dead.

158
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,640
My aunt really would be dead?

159
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,519
Why are you saying this?

160
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,920
Stop lying to make me
go back and be Ms. Claire.

161
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,560
I'm not lying.

162
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:26,960
- Your aunt is still alive.
- I don't believe you.

163
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:29,640
My aunt was hit by a car.

164
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:31,879
She's dead now.

165
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:35,080
She's not here anymore. Do you hear me?

166
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,680
Aunt.

167
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:07,360
She's really still alive?

168
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:11,720
If you calm down and listen to me,

169
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:14,320
I'll let you see your aunt.

170
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:26,080
Make sure and update me. Understood?

171
00:15:37,760 --> 00:15:39,160
What is it?

172
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:41,039
Don't act dumb.

173
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,279
‎How did it go
‎after you followed Chan last night?

174
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:44,440
Did you find Claire?

175
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:47,240
- No.
- Why not?

176
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:48,840
Or...

177
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:52,680
did he know you were
following him, so he hid her?

178
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,320
What is wrong with you?

179
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,640
Are you that afraid she'll be back?

180
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,480
Aren't you afraid?

181
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:05,039
If you're not, you should be.

182
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:07,280
Even now, while she's gone,

183
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:10,160
Mr. Thiwa barely acknowledges you and me.

184
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:13,279
What do you think will happen to us

185
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:15,000
if Chan's bringing her back?

186
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,200
Nothing will happen.

187
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:21,279
Because if everything
Chan told me last night is true,

188
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:23,280
Claire will never come back.

189
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,240
What do you mean?

190
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:09,000
Aunt.

191
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,079
I came to see you.

192
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,480
Can you hear me?

193
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:18,640
These are my hands.

194
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,599
It's me, Aunt.

195
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:31,920
Aunt.

196
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:34,800
Please wake up and talk to me.

197
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,320
Aunt.

198
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:47,480
I'm sorry.

199
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:52,880
If only I'd come to see you sooner...

200
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:05,920
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Aunt. I'm sorry.

201
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,600
What happened?

202
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,560
Why is my aunt here?

203
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:32,320
I had her moved here.

204
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,520
While you were recovering,

205
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:39,360
we tried to contact her
to tell her about the helicopter crash.

206
00:18:40,080 --> 00:18:42,720
That's how we found out
she'd been hit by a car.

207
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:45,280
Her condition was quite serious,

208
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:48,160
so I had her transferred here.

209
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,880
Why did you save my aunt?

210
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:57,680
Then let's be honest with each other.

211
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:00,400
I saved your aunt

212
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:03,480
because I needed you to be Claire.

213
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,919
And as long as you go along with it,

214
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:11,080
your aunt will get the best care.

215
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:14,640
‎Are you using
‎my aunt's life to threaten me?

216
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:17,560
Yes.

217
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,280
You...

218
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,440
How could you do this?

219
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,640
You already took my life.

220
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:28,480
Now you're threatening me
with my aunt's life.

221
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,560
How...

222
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,320
How can you be this cruel?

223
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:37,440
Before you let your anger take over,

224
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,479
maybe you should hear my offer.

225
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,680
Huh?

226
00:19:44,040 --> 00:19:46,319
As long as you agree to be Claire,

227
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:50,200
I promise I'll find the best doctors
to treat your aunt.

228
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,600
We'll make sure she wakes up.

229
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:54,919
And after she wakes up,

230
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:59,720
she'll stay at the best Alzheimer's
care center for the rest of her life.

231
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:04,760
And I'll cover all the expenses.

232
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:07,879
As for you,

233
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:10,520
after the chairman passes away,

234
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:13,240
I'll give you 20 million.

235
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,680
And you can live your own life.

236
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:22,120
What do you mean, live my own life?

237
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:25,080
I need you to be Claire

238
00:20:26,360 --> 00:20:28,960
because I'm worried about
the chairman's heart condition.

239
00:20:30,760 --> 00:20:33,880
But once he passes away,

240
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:37,240
I won't need you anymore.

241
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:45,360
What if I refuse?

242
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:50,760
If I refuse to be Ms. Claire,
the chairman will die.

243
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:53,320
A life for a life.

244
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:58,280
Then you'll know
how it feels to lose someone.

245
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:05,959
Come in.

246
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,040
‎What do you need me for, Cha?

247
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,800
I was thinking...

248
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:15,640
of appointing you as
the new Chief Technology Officer.

249
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:17,640
Me?

250
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:19,119
Of course.

251
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:21,639
And if I become CEO,

252
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:24,160
how could I let my man
remain a mere architect?

253
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:27,079
CEO?

254
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:29,960
- But that position belongs to--
- Claire.

255
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:31,559
I'm aware.

256
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:33,920
But soon it will be mine.

257
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:36,640
What would happen to Ms. Claire?

258
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:46,159
<i>If Ms. Cha told the chairman,</i>

259
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:48,919
- wouldn't he...?
- We can't ever let him find out.

260
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:50,679
I'll look for Jinla myself.

261
00:21:50,680 --> 00:21:52,759
You keep an eye on the chairman.

262
00:21:52,760 --> 00:21:55,360
<i>Don't let Ms. Cha tell him about this.</i>

263
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,279
Hello, Chan?

264
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:03,160
How's it going? Did you find her?

265
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:06,319
What?

266
00:22:06,320 --> 00:22:08,280
- Honey?
- What is it?

267
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:11,720
Is Chan really bringing Claire back?

268
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:15,280
What if everything he said is a lie?

269
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:17,800
Say what you have to say.

270
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:20,160
Claire might be...

271
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:25,400
Mr. Chairman.

272
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,120
Is Chan here?

273
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:36,680
‎Honey, Tun may have come
‎to tell us something else.

274
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,880
Well? Chan can't come, can he?

275
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:42,680
‎I'll tell you the truth, Chris.

276
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:45,400
Claire is dead.

277
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:51,200
I'm only telling you this
because you and she used to be lovers.

278
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:53,880
She died in the helicopter crash.

279
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:57,800
I just came to tell you that...

280
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:04,280
Mr. Chan has brought Ms. Claire here.

281
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,559
<i>What if I refuse?</i>

282
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:32,600
If I refuse to be Ms. Claire,

283
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,439
the chairman will die.

284
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:36,719
A life for a life.

285
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:40,640
Then you'll know
how it feels to lose someone.

286
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:45,360
Are you sure?

287
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:50,799
Do you want to know
why I wanted you to know

288
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,720
what you'd get if you agreed?

289
00:23:56,440 --> 00:24:00,720
‎Because you think
‎money can buy everything.

290
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,360
That's partly true.

291
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,480
‎But I told you what you'd get
‎if you agreed to be Claire

292
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:11,640
so you wouldn't find out what you'd lose.

293
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,319
Do you know how much it costs

294
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:18,559
‎for your aunt's treatment here
‎every minute?

295
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:19,480
Huh?

296
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:24,120
Doctors' fees, medical bills,
room fees, medication.

297
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:27,760
Let me give you a rough number.

298
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:32,120
‎Your aunt needs
‎at least 500,000 baht a month

299
00:24:33,080 --> 00:24:34,960
just to keep breathing.

300
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,320
Think it over.

301
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:53,160
I'm glad you agreed.

302
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,120
I had no choice.

303
00:24:58,120 --> 00:24:59,560
Let's go see your grandfather.

304
00:25:12,960 --> 00:25:14,000
Claire!

305
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:24,520
<i>Grandpa.</i>

306
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:28,680
<i>So this is
Ms. Claire's beloved grandfather.</i>

307
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:55,560
Let me take a closer look.

308
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,480
I'm sorry.

309
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:16,400
Claire.

310
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:28,280
Don't leave me for this long again.

311
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,440
Exactly.

312
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:36,760
It's been so long,
I thought you weren't coming back.

313
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,840
I'll go check
that everything is ready inside.

314
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,440
Welcome home.

315
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:09,280
Let's go inside.

316
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,960
I'm glad you're back, Ms. Claire.

317
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:24,680
Claire.

318
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:28,080
Go inside with your grandfather.

319
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:35,080
Come on, let's go.

320
00:27:44,760 --> 00:27:48,279
<i>‎Do you know how much it costs</i>

321
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,639
‎for your aunt's treatment here
‎every minute?

322
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:53,040
‎Your aunt needs
‎at least 500,000 baht a month

323
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:55,440
<i>just to keep breathing.</i>

324
00:27:58,240 --> 00:27:59,760
<i>What am I afraid of?</i>

325
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,400
<i>Why don't I want to enter this house?</i>

326
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,400
<i>I know what I'm afraid of.</i>

327
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:11,000
<i>I'm afraid of becoming someone else.</i>

328
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,960
<i>Because the moment I step into this house,</i>

329
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:22,160
<i>my name won't be Jinla anymore.</i>

330
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:27,759
<i>"My name is Jinla.</i>

331
00:28:27,760 --> 00:28:29,440
I'm your niece, Aunt Lin."

332
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:33,200
<i>But I will be...</i>

333
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:37,680
Claire?

334
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:44,160
Has anything here changed?

335
00:28:49,560 --> 00:28:50,800
No.

336
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:53,840
Then sit with me over there.

337
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:06,200
Is something wrong, Claire?

338
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:13,480
She's probably tired, sir.

339
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:18,759
Claire, do you want to go
and talk to your grandfather

340
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:20,480
or go upstairs and rest?

341
00:29:24,280 --> 00:29:25,400
It's alright.

342
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:29,120
Take her to rest.

343
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:32,199
We can talk later this evening.

344
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:34,280
Come down and have dinner with me.

345
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:37,440
Okay.

346
00:29:40,360 --> 00:29:42,000
I'm glad to see you're alright.

347
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:49,560
Go, Chan. Take her to rest.

348
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:04,239
Well?

349
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:08,239
How does it feel
knowing your former lover is dead?

350
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:09,640
Cha.

351
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:13,799
I told you I don't like it
when you talk like this.

352
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:15,840
There was nothing between me and Claire.

353
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:18,159
You're the only one for me.

354
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:20,159
I don't believe you.

355
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:21,240
Cha.

356
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,120
Cha.

357
00:30:24,800 --> 00:30:26,360
I'll make you believe me.

358
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:47,320
MOM
SLIDE TO ANSWER

359
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:52,920
Yes?

360
00:30:56,320 --> 00:30:57,200
What?

361
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,800
Get out. I'll call you later.

362
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,040
What did you say, Mom?

363
00:31:21,840 --> 00:31:24,240
Chan was the one who said Claire was dead.

364
00:31:25,320 --> 00:31:27,280
So how could he bring her home?

365
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:32,039
Hey.

366
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:36,400
Then see for yourself whether I'm joking.

367
00:31:45,840 --> 00:31:46,879
<i>Well?</i>

368
00:31:46,880 --> 00:31:50,519
<i>Are you still going to
accuse me of joking around?</i>

369
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:51,560
Claire?

370
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:54,560
Why isn't she dead?

371
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:56,800
I should be asking you that.

372
00:31:57,360 --> 00:31:59,840
You're so stupid, you let Chan fool you.

373
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:08,920
Claire isn't dead?

374
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:25,920
Hey.

375
00:32:26,760 --> 00:32:28,040
What?

376
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,959
Do you want everyone to know
you're not Claire?

377
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:35,759
Well... What am I supposed to do?

378
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:38,319
That was my first time being Ms. Claire.

379
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:39,880
I didn't know how to act.

380
00:32:41,360 --> 00:32:42,280
First,

381
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,439
we will never talk
about you not being Claire.

382
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:46,879
Second,

383
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,920
‎You must call the Chairman "Grandpa."

384
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:52,319
I'm not used to it. How can I--

385
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:57,080
If you want to be safe here,
do as I say and stop arguing.

386
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,720
As for tonight,

387
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:07,320
you will sleep in this room.

388
00:33:27,720 --> 00:33:30,320
Hey, I can sleep on this sofa.

389
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:35,040
Why?

390
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:38,919
Well, it's Ms. Claire's bed.

391
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:41,399
Even if I look like her, I'm not her.

392
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:42,560
Are you scared?

393
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:47,200
Hey, let go of me. Hey.

394
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:49,520
Why?

395
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:53,720
Are you scared to sleep here
because it's a dead woman's bed?

396
00:34:00,880 --> 00:34:04,480
But I think Claire would be happy

397
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:06,480
that you became her.

398
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,440
Happy that I became her?

399
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:12,560
Of course.

400
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:17,400
Thanks to you, her grandfather is fine.

401
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:28,960
Can I go look inside that room?

402
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:38,279
You can go into any room in this house

403
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,600
because everything belongs to you.

404
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:18,079
Hey, how much are all these worth?

405
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:19,160
Oops.

406
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:27,279
Hey, you're hurting me.

407
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:29,840
You asked me how much all these are worth.

408
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:34,680
Do you know what will happen
if you ask me that again?

409
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,120
Hey.

410
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:51,120
If you've seen enough, come with me.

411
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,640
You have a job to do.

412
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:08,760
This tablet has all of
Claire's personal information.

413
00:36:09,480 --> 00:36:12,039
Memorize everything before dinner.

414
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,120
What?

415
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:16,599
You want me to memorize
everything about Ms. Claire?

416
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:18,360
How am I supposed to do that?

417
00:36:23,240 --> 00:36:24,319
Fine.

418
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:26,279
I'll do my best.

419
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:28,759
- That's all I can promise.
- No.

420
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:30,640
You have to memorize all of it.

421
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:33,279
‎Because if you make a mistake,

422
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:35,680
‎everyone in this house
‎will be ready to kill you.

423
00:36:37,600 --> 00:36:39,879
You don't have to make it sound so scary.

424
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:42,559
‎And who exactly are the people
‎in this house you're talking about?

425
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:44,200
Ms. Rossarin?

426
00:36:44,880 --> 00:36:48,280
She hasn't done anything to me
like you warned me earlier.

427
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:51,600
Just do as I say.

428
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:54,879
If you really want me to be her,

429
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:58,320
then you have to tell me
why Ms. Rossarin hates me.

430
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:10,000
Because Claire thought
Ms. Rossarin had killed her parents.

431
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:19,240
Grandpa.

432
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:22,080
Oh. Come here.

433
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:30,080
Why are you hiding these?

434
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:34,960
You don't have to hide them.
I know everything.

435
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:37,399
Why did you fight with your classmates?

436
00:37:37,400 --> 00:37:40,920
Because they kept saying
I don't have a mom or a dad.

437
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:46,919
How about this?

438
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:49,159
I'll go to school with you tomorrow.

439
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:51,439
That way, you can tell your classmates

440
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:54,519
Aunt Rin and I are your mom and your dad.

441
00:37:54,520 --> 00:37:56,799
Then they'll stop teasing you.

442
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:59,240
- Really?
- Of course.

443
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:01,799
But you have to tell Aunt Rin first.

444
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:03,000
Okay.

445
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:10,160
Go on. Go tell Aunt Rin.

446
00:38:23,160 --> 00:38:24,320
Aunt Rin?

447
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:29,120
Are you free tomorrow?

448
00:38:30,680 --> 00:38:32,120
Aunt Rin?

449
00:38:36,000 --> 00:38:36,919
What is it?

450
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:41,239
I wanted to know if you're free tomorrow.

451
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:44,400
Could you take me to school?

452
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:48,000
Why do I have to take you?

453
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:50,160
Don't we have a driver?

454
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:54,440
I want you to be there as my mom. Please.

455
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:56,600
What?

456
00:38:57,560 --> 00:38:59,840
Hey, are you insane?

457
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:02,039
Go away.

458
00:39:02,040 --> 00:39:04,040
Didn't you see I was enjoying myself?

459
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:09,999
My classmates called me an orphan,

460
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:12,280
so I want you to be there as my mom.

461
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:16,239
Please, Aunt Rin.

462
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:17,640
Please.

463
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:20,679
I told you to leave me alone.

464
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:22,520
Are you deaf?

465
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:25,080
I said no, no, no, no, no!

466
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:29,800
Actually, your classmates
were right, weren't they?

467
00:39:30,520 --> 00:39:33,840
You really don't have a mom or a dad.

468
00:39:34,520 --> 00:39:36,799
No. That's not true.

469
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:40,040
No. No.

470
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:42,840
Shut up.

471
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:48,640
Do you want to die like your parents? Huh?

472
00:39:56,680 --> 00:40:00,280
Claire's parents went missing
during a river cruise in France.

473
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:03,240
Everyone thought it was an accident.

474
00:40:04,560 --> 00:40:05,480
Except Claire.

475
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:09,719
Why did Ms. Claire think that?

476
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:12,280
That tablet has everything about her.

477
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:17,720
Things she likes and dislikes,
her friends, her schools.

478
00:40:18,920 --> 00:40:22,160
I also included
her private Facebook and Instagram

479
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:25,080
so you can see Claire's lifestyle.

480
00:40:31,240 --> 00:40:32,599
Hold... Hold on.

481
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:36,560
You only took screenshots of
her Instagram and Facebook for me?

482
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:41,320
‎I thought you'd actually let me use
‎Ms. Claire's Facebook and Instagram.

483
00:40:42,160 --> 00:40:43,600
I don't trust you.

484
00:40:44,720 --> 00:40:47,639
Only three people know you're not Claire.

485
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:49,480
You, me, and Tunlathon.

486
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:51,880
To prevent any risk,

487
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:56,240
you're not allowed to use
any communication devices or the internet.

488
00:40:57,920 --> 00:40:59,520
Now memorize her information.

489
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:01,520
Dinner is coming.

490
00:41:10,160 --> 00:41:12,960
Are you crazy?
All you do is order me around.

491
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:26,120
Tun.

492
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,360
What did you need?

493
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:34,080
I got more findings
from the police about the crash.

494
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:35,840
What did you find?

495
00:41:37,320 --> 00:41:38,840
The engine worked properly.

496
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:42,000
The pilot didn't report
any problems before the crash.

497
00:41:43,280 --> 00:41:45,360
But there's something suspicious.

498
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:50,320
I want you to ask Ms. Jinla
what really happened.

499
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,319
Let's leave that for now.

500
00:41:54,320 --> 00:41:57,879
Right now, I want her
to focus on becoming Claire.

501
00:41:57,880 --> 00:41:59,280
Anything else can wait.

502
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:03,480
Do you think the chairman
will suspect she isn't Claire?

503
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:32,240
So this is why Ms. Claire
loved her grandfather so much.

504
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,640
At least...

505
00:42:35,560 --> 00:42:37,640
you and I are both orphans.

506
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:42,400
Don't worry about me, Aunt.

507
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:48,200
This is nothing. I can handle it.

508
00:43:14,320 --> 00:43:15,479
What did you make today?

509
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:18,239
Today we have pork rolls,

510
00:43:18,240 --> 00:43:20,879
smoked pork ribs,

511
00:43:20,880 --> 00:43:22,680
and hobo dinner.

512
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:25,400
- Thank you.
- Yes, sir.

513
00:43:26,280 --> 00:43:30,039
‎Mr. Chan and Ms. Claire
‎haven't arrived yet?

514
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:33,960
How rude. They shouldn't keep
their elders waiting at the table.

515
00:43:35,320 --> 00:43:36,360
Go get them.

516
00:43:37,080 --> 00:43:38,439
No need.

517
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:41,000
Claire just got out of the hospital.

518
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:44,400
Must be hard for her to walk.
Don't make a big deal out of it.

519
00:43:46,960 --> 00:43:49,520
Is Cha back yet? Did you tell her?

520
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,440
Mom told me.

521
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:55,879
Sit down.

522
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:58,239
But I can't join you today.

523
00:43:58,240 --> 00:43:59,639
I feel nauseous.

524
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:02,040
Eh? What's wrong, Cha?

525
00:44:03,360 --> 00:44:04,719
I don't know.

526
00:44:04,720 --> 00:44:07,200
Something suddenly smells rotten.

527
00:44:08,360 --> 00:44:09,800
I'll go up to my room.

528
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:26,320
Claire.

529
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:30,919
<i>Alicha is Ms. Rossarin's daughter.</i>

530
00:44:30,920 --> 00:44:33,279
She's around Claire's age.

531
00:44:33,280 --> 00:44:36,680
She's stubborn
and doesn't get along with Claire.

532
00:44:43,160 --> 00:44:44,240
Hello, Ms. Cha.

533
00:44:49,880 --> 00:44:51,600
Are you hallucinating?

534
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:53,600
What's with the polite greeting?

535
00:44:54,200 --> 00:44:58,360
Or is your brain still scrambled
after coming back from the dead?

536
00:44:59,240 --> 00:45:02,760
You must mean
when I told you Claire was dead.

537
00:45:03,360 --> 00:45:07,040
I said that for Claire's safety.

538
00:45:07,640 --> 00:45:09,239
But if it made you misunderstand,

539
00:45:09,240 --> 00:45:10,680
I must apologize.

540
00:45:12,080 --> 00:45:13,880
That's enough! Today is a good day!

541
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:16,839
Claire is home now.

542
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:18,400
Why are you guys arguing?

543
00:45:20,920 --> 00:45:22,000
Arguing?

544
00:45:23,480 --> 00:45:26,800
Don't you remember
what Claire did to me before the crash?

545
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:31,639
<i>Cha, I didn't do anything.</i>

546
00:45:31,640 --> 00:45:34,720
<i>You didn't do anything?!
You didn't do anything?!</i>

547
00:45:39,160 --> 00:45:42,840
I know we had our differences.

548
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:44,960
But let's start over.

549
00:45:50,880 --> 00:45:52,360
Is this funny to you?

550
00:45:53,200 --> 00:45:55,640
Cha. What are you doing?

551
00:45:56,560 --> 00:45:58,280
She's trying to be civil.

552
00:45:59,960 --> 00:46:02,440
When will you stop going after her
like a rabid dog?

553
00:46:04,320 --> 00:46:05,400
Will this end here?

554
00:46:07,680 --> 00:46:09,840
If not, I'll settle it myself.

555
00:46:17,800 --> 00:46:18,800
This ends here.

556
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:23,600
But she has to let me slap her.

557
00:46:25,480 --> 00:46:27,280
I actually wanted to slap you back then,

558
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:29,600
but the crash happened.

559
00:46:30,480 --> 00:46:33,320
Well? Are you ready to start over?

560
00:46:35,320 --> 00:46:36,560
Just once.

561
00:46:42,920 --> 00:46:44,520
I can't let you do that.

562
00:46:47,440 --> 00:46:49,279
You have no right to touch me.

563
00:46:49,280 --> 00:46:50,960
I wouldn't have stopped you

564
00:46:51,520 --> 00:46:54,720
if she could remember what she did to you.

565
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:02,760
What do you mean?

566
00:47:09,480 --> 00:47:11,360
Claire is suffering from amnesia.

567
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:16,480
What?

568
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:18,160
Amnesia?

569
00:47:20,280 --> 00:47:21,599
That's right, sir.

570
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:24,119
During the helicopter crash,

571
00:47:24,120 --> 00:47:29,120
Claire's brain suffered trauma,
causing her amnesia.

572
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:34,120
And I brought her home
on the doctor's advice.

573
00:47:34,760 --> 00:47:39,120
The doctor said being somewhere familiar

574
00:47:39,720 --> 00:47:42,360
might help bring her memories back.

575
00:47:44,840 --> 00:47:46,679
Don't worry, Ms. Cha.

576
00:47:46,680 --> 00:47:49,960
Once Claire remembers what she did to you,

577
00:47:50,800 --> 00:47:53,200
I'll make sure she'll make it up to you.

578
00:47:58,960 --> 00:48:00,280
Claire.

579
00:48:07,360 --> 00:48:08,320
Claire.

580
00:48:10,600 --> 00:48:11,760
Do you remember me?

581
00:48:21,920 --> 00:48:23,120
Just be safe...

582
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:27,640
and live in this house with me,
that's enough.

583
00:48:30,960 --> 00:48:32,080
Yes, Grandpa.

584
00:49:03,680 --> 00:49:05,079
You want me to fake amnesia?

585
00:49:05,080 --> 00:49:07,639
The amnesia excuse won't work forever.

586
00:49:07,640 --> 00:49:11,199
<i>No matter what, you have to be
as much like Claire as possible</i>

587
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:13,319
because you must become
TGL Group's chairwoman.

588
00:49:13,320 --> 00:49:16,720
You're launching the project
when the project lead is in that state?

589
00:49:17,600 --> 00:49:20,040
Don't you worry. I want Claire dead too.

590
00:49:20,960 --> 00:49:22,240
<i>In that case,</i>

591
00:49:22,880 --> 00:49:24,400
I'll kill her myself.

592
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:27,439
RECOMMENDED SAUNA TEMPERATURE
50-60 DEGREES CELSIUS FOR YOUR SAFETY

593
00:49:27,440 --> 00:49:30,040
Help me! Please open the door!
